name: BOEING 747-8 FREIGHTER ACTION! Cargolux and Korean Air Cargo at Calgary Airport
description:
Thank you to RadarBox for supporting this plane spotting video! Find out more about them at https://www.radarbox.com/?referrer=AlexAviation

About a year ago, two Boeing 747-8Fs paid a visit to Calgary International Airport - one from Korean Air Cargo, and another from Cargolux.

The Cargolux one was coming in on their regular scheduled service, but with a rare daylight arrival in some gorgeous sunset lighting. The Korean Air Cargo was a scheduled flight, departing in the early summer morning hours (around 5AM).

Both aircraft were quite a few hours apart in their visits, but it's still not often we get to see two of Boeing's largest freighter in daylight in the same day! Enjoy this 747-8F action.
